fix: task dispatcher infinite retry loop. When the harness returned errors (CLI crash, exit code 1), the dispatcher saved the error text as an 'assistant' message and looped back to BuildPrompt. 15+ turns of the same error with no circuit breaker. Root causes: (1) Legacy send_task fallback silently consumed errors. Removed it — if session endpoint fails, task fails immediately. (2) DriverResult::Failed didn't update task status — task stayed in_progress and got re-dispatched by recover_on_startup. Now sets status to 'cancelled'. (3) Removed unused model field from Context (was only used by legacy path). No backward compat needed — v0 before first release.
